                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It is early days yet, but so far I am finding a coercer increasingly difficult to solo. It is not so much whether I can kill the mob or not, it is will root hold long enough for me to kill it. Caster mobs are becoming very difficult, as if I spend the time to negate their casting then I do not have enough time to nuke before root breaks. At 26 there are a few grey 2 uparrow mobs I cannot kill and anything higher than grey better have no arrows or at least one down arrow.
<br />

<br />
Assuming that DoTs do not break root as much as nukes do, then it would appear that an illusionist would be slightly better at soloing. This opinion is further reinforced by the coercer getting a few extra group friendly spells.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
